Selenium Webdriver
-----------------------
what is webdriver?
-> webdriver is one of the component in selenium
-> webdriver is module  (in python)(interface in java)
module contains classes and variables

chrome browser - > Chrome etc

-> webdriver is an API
selenium architecture -

Locators -
identify webelement
action

locatores -
tag name and class name - mostly used when we want select multiple webelements

id,linktext and partial linktext - used when we want select single webelement

css selector -
1) tag and id -> tag is optional here
syntax-> tagname#valueOfId or #value of id

2) tag and class -
syntax - tag.valueof class or .value of class

3) tag and attribute -
syntax - input[attibute=value] or [attribute=value]

4) tag , class, and attribute
syntax - input.valueof class[attibute=value]

xpath -
two types of xpath is there -1) absolute 2) relative
absolute xpath - it starts from the root html node
- starts with single slash
- we use only tag nodes
- syntax - /html/body/div[1]/li[1]/a
- disadv - if developer add new element or changed location of variable then this xpath will broken.
address of a webelement

1) and - if both element matches with html then only element will be found
syntax - //tagname[@attribute name = 'value' and @attribute name = 'value']

2) or - if one of the element matches in the html then only element will be found
syntax - //tagname[@attribute name = 'value' or @attribute name ='value']

3) contains - element will be identified if part of attribute value is given.
it is used when we want to find dynamic webelements
syntax - //*[contains(@attribute name = '')
//tagname[contains(@attribute name = 'substring')

4) starts-with - element will be identified if any attribute value is start with given value.
syntax - //*[starts-with(@attribute value,'')]
//tagname[starts-with(@attribute value,'ab')]

5) text - we can find element on the basis of inner text.
syntax - //tagname[text()="inner text "]





